out%20critical%20discussion%20or%20appropriate%20reflection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%2010%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20amidst%20uproar%2C%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Speaker%2C%20Vice-President%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%2C%20passed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-pharmacy-amendment-bill-2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20Pharmacy%20(Amendment)%20Bill%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20three%20minutes%20from%20the%20time%20it%20was%20called%20for%20vote%2C%20without%20even%20the%20audible%20%E2%80%98aye%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20parliamentarians.%20What%20one%20could%20hear%20was%20a%20loud%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99%20when%20the%20vote%20was%20called.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERead%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20details%20of%20the%20newly%20introduced%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill.%20This%20Bill%20comes%20despite%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20earlier%20this%20year%20while%20examining%20Article%20324(2)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvfU9fPDj1W%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvfU9fPDj1W%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Cspan%3Es%3C%2Fspan%3Eaid%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FvfU9fPDj1W%5C%22%3Ethat%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ECs%20shall%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Csubject%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20any%20law%20made%20in%20that%20%5Bon%20behalf%20of%20the%5D%20Parliament%2C%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20law%20scholar%20Gautam%20Bhatia%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20and%20jurisprudential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F03%2F03%2Fdecoding-the-supreme-courts-election-commission-judgment-i%2F%5C%22%3Einterpretation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgautambhatia88%2Fstatus%2F1689703854529536000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20SC%20judgment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20SC%20did%20not%20say%20that%20the%20CJI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20be%20on%20the%20appointments%20committee%20under%20the%20future%20law.%20Thus%2C%20the%20mere%20fact%20that%20the%20new%20bill%20removes%20the%20CJI%20is%20not%20the%20reason%20why%20it%E2%80%99s%20bad.%20But%20nor%20did%20SC%20say%20that%20%3Cem%3Eany%3C%2Fem%3E%20law%20would%20be%20consistent%20with%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20law%20would%20have%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20EC%20was%20adequately%20insulated%20from%20executive%20dominance%2C%20because%20the%20referee%20has%20to%20be%20impartial.%20The%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20obviously%20fails%20that%20test.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20thus%20one%20insidious%20way%20in%20which%20the%20current%20regime%20has%20used%20legislative%20and%20other%20institutionalised%20apparatus%20to%20further%20its%20agenda%20of%20establishing%20centralised%20and%20consolidated%20control.%20Presence%20of%20legal%20voids%20%E2%80%93%20say%20from%20recent%20or%20previous%20SC%20judgments%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20makes%20its%20path%20less%20embroiled%20with%20challenges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20Monsoon%20Session%20presented%20three%20highlights%2C%20all%20signalling%20a%20crisis%20of%20accountability%20and%20an%20over-centralised%20executive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20was%20the%20evocation%20of%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0ethnic%20conflict%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20response%20solicited%20by%20the%20opposition%20from%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20while%20attributing%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccountability.%20%E2%80%98Accountability%E2%80%99%20is%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20word%20used%20less%20now%20in%20the%20democratic%20order%20of%20contemporary%20governance%20affairs%20but%20it%20is%20important%20nonetheless.%20Opposition%20MPs%20demanded%20action%20from%20those%20in%20power%20against%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%20for%20what%20has%20happened%20in%20the%20state%20over%20the%20last%20three%20months.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Manipur%20should%20have%20perhaps%20taken%20centre%20stage%20this%20Monsoon%20Session.%20The%20Union%20government%20should%20have%20addressed%20questions%20on%20its%20own%20accountability%2C%20while%20discussing%20key%20concerns%20of%20the%20state%20of%20governance%20in%20a%20BJP-governed%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-tribal-politics-behind-manipur-conflict%5C%22%3EThe%20Tribal%20Politics%20Behind%20the%20Manipur%20Conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecond%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0was%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FDigital%2520Personal%2520Data%2520Protection%2520Bill%2C%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20legislation%20is%20going%20to%20have%20enormous%20ramifications.%20For%20example%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20key%20limitations%20is%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20exemptions%20provided%20to%20data%20processing%20by%20the%20state%20on%20grounds%20such%20as%20national%20security%2C%20which%20may%20lead%20to%20data%20collection%2C%20processing%2C%20and%20retention%20beyond%20what%20is%20necessary.%20%C2%A0This%20will%20violate%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieindia.org%2F2023%2F08%2F09%2Fdata-protection-in-india-%257C-land-titling-reforms-and-litigation-in-benin-pub-90355%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0recent%20essay%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20Suyash%20Rai%20and%20Anirudh%20Burman%2C%20from%20Carnegie%20India%2C%20is%20a%20must%20read.%20They%20explain%20how%20the%202023%20DPDP%20(Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection)%20Bill%20is%20very%20different%20from%20the%202018%20bill%2C%20whereby%2C%20there%20are%20aspects%20of%20this%20(current)%20bill%20that%20could%20%E2%80%9Cpotentially%20limit%20its%20efficacy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFirst%2C%20the%20exemptions%20given%20in%20the%20bill%20and%20the%20power%20to%20give%20more%20exemptions%20are%20so%20expansive%20that%20practically%20anyone%20and%20any%20processing%20activity%20can%20be%20exempted.%20In%20addition%20to%20an%20almost%20complete%20exemption%20for%20government%20bodies%2C%20the%20bill%20also%20envisages%20broad%20powers%20to%20exempt%20other%20entities.%20Consider%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20clause%2017(5)%2C%20which%20seeks%20to%20empower%20the%20central%20government%20to%2C%20before%20the%20expiry%20of%20five%20years%20from%20the%20date%20of%20commencement%20of%20this%20law%2C%20declare%20that%20any%20provision%20of%20the%20law%20shall%20not%20apply%20to%20such%20entity%20processing%20the%20data%20or%20any%20classes%20of%20such%20entities%20for%20such%20period%20as%20may%20be%20specified%20in%20the%20notification.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20government%20can%20completely%20exempt%20any%20entity%20without%20any%20guidance%20in%20the%20legislation%20on%20the%20basis%20for%20such%20an%20exemption.%20When%20such%20powers%20are%20given%20to%20the%20government%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%20there%20are%20some%20criteria%20stated%20in%20the%20law%20to%20guide%20the%20decision%20to%20exempt%2C%20but%20no%20such%20criteria%20have%20been%20provided%20in%20the%20bill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSecond%2C%20the%20proposed%20data%20protection%20board%20would%20have%20no%20regulatory%20or%20supervisory%20powers%2C%20and%20almost%20all%20the%20rules%20and%20regulations%20would%20be%20made%20by%20the%20government.%20Giving%20such%20responsibilities%20to%20a%20ministry%20of%20the%20government%20is%20a%20questionable%20move%E2%80%94to%20do%20this%20well%2C%20it%20will%20have%20to%20build%20considerable%20capabilities%20that%20are%20easier%20to%20build%20in%20a%20separate%20agency.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20board%20would%20have%20little%20incentive%20to%20build%20technical%20capabilities%20that%20could%20be%20useful%20for%20regulating%20the%20digital%20economy%20from%20a%20data%20protection%20perspective.%20The%20board%20will%20also%20have%20less%20independence%20than%20other%20public%20authorities%20in%20India.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20chairperson%20and%20members%20would%20be%20appointed%20for%20two%20years%20and%20may%20be%20reappointed%20thereafter%2C%20while%20the%20standard%20practice%20is%20to%20appoint%20such%20authorities%20for%20three%20or%20five%20years.%20A%20short%20duration%20of%20appointment%20typically%20hampers%20independence%20from%20the%20government%20because%20reappointment%20can%20be%20used%20as%20a%20bargaining%20chip.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThird%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20the%20individuals%20whose%20personal%20data%20is%20to%20be%20protected%20will%20be%20worse%20off.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20bill%20seeks%20to%20amend%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20to%20do%20away%20with%20the%20provision%20on%20compensation%20to%20be%20provided%20to%20the%20affected%20person%20in%20situations%20where%2C%20due%20to%20negligence%20in%20implementing%20and%20maintaining%20reasonable%20security%20practices%20and%20procedures%2C%20a%20wrongful%20loss%20is%20caused%20to%20a%20person%20or%20a%20wrongful%20gain%20is%20made.%20The%20DPDP%20Bill%20does%20not%20provide%20for%20any%20compensation%20to%20such%20affected%20persons.%20As%20an%20aside%2C%20the%20bill%20also%20seeks%20to%20amend%20the%20right%20to%20information%20law%20to%20prohibit%20the%20release%20of%20any%20personal%20information%2C%20which%20is%20a%20considerable%20dilution%20of%20the%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20serious%20issues%20that%20perhaps%20did%20not%20get%20enough%20attention%20this%20Monsoon%20Session%20before%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Bill%20has%20become%20Law%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20will%20get%20most%20of%20the%20powers%20to%20define%20and%20exercise%20the%20scope%20of%20its%20application%20and%20the%20substance%20of%20data%20protection%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-diary-parts-of-rahul-gandhis-speech-expunged-and-missing-sansad-tv-camera-angles%5C%22%3EParliament%20Diary%3A%20Parts%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Speech%20Expunged%20and%20Missing%20Sansad%20TV%20Camera%20Angles%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThird%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20was%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FGNCTD(Amendment)_Bill_2023_Bill_Text.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGovernment%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20Bill%2C%20as%20intensely%20debated%20in%20both%20Houses%20of%20the%20parliament%2C%20raises%20constitutional%20concerns%20of%20legislative%20over-reach%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20on%20the%20powers%20vested%20in%20an%20elected%20state%20government.%20The%20Bill%2C%20soon%20to%20become%20law%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Econfers%20powers%20over%20the%20transfer%20and%20posting%20of%20officers%20to%20the%20National%20Capital%20Civil%20Services%20Authority%20(which%20consists%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20Chief%20Secretary%20of%20Delhi%2C%20and%20Principal%20Home%20Secretary%20of%20Delhi)%20that%20may%20break%20the%20triple%20chain%20of%20accountability%20that%20links%20the%20civil%20services%2C%20ministers%2C%20the%20legislature%2C%20and%20citizens.%20This%20shall%20violate%20the%20principle%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstitutionnet.org%2Fvl%2Fitem%2Fbasic-structure-indian-constitution%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebasic%20structure%20doctrine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20lot%20has%20been%20written%20and%20said%20about%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eunconstitutionality%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20t%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20Bill%20which%20empowers%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20or%20LG%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Super%20CM%E2%80%99%20with%20the%20power%20to%20exercise%20his%20sole%20discretion%20on%20several%20matters%20including%20those%20recommended%20by%20the%20National%20Capital%20Civil%20Services%20Authority%2C%20and%20the%20summoning%2C%20prorogation%20and%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Delhi%20legislative%20assembly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20authorises%20department%20secretaries%20to%20bring%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20LG%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20and%20the%20chief%20secretary%2C%20any%20matter%20that%20may%20bring%20the%20Delhi%20government%20into%20controversy%20with%20the%20Union%20government.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20passing%2C%20and%20it%20becoming%20a%20law%2C%20means%20that%20the%20elected%20government%20in%20Delhi%20and%20its%20chief%20minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20will%20even%20lose%20their%20power%20to%20convene%20a%20meeting%20or%20session%20with%20concerned%20authorities%20to%20conduct%20essential%20government%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20LG%E2%80%99s%20power%20will%20reign%20supreme%20as%20most%20department%20secretaries%20will%20now%20bring%20certain%20matters%20directly%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20LG%2C%20chief%20minister%20or%20chief%20secretary%2C%20without%20consulting%20the%20concerned%20minister.%20This%20will%20go%20against%20the%20collective%20responsibility%20of%20the%20elected%20state%20cabinet%2C%20as%20the%20concerned%20ministers%20cannot%20provide%20inputs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20opposing%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20Congress%20leader%20and%20senior%20advocate%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fpolitics%2Fnews%2Fcontrol-freak-sarkar-what-congs-abhishek-manu-singhvi-said-during-delhi-services-bill-discussion-11691408691248.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C(This%20Bill%20leads%20to%20the)%20creation%20of%20an%20authority%20where%20the%20chief%20minister%20is%20in%20a%20minority%2C%20to%20empower%20two%20bureaucrats%20to%20overrule%20an%20elected%20chief%20minister%20and%20make%20the%20LG%2C%20a%20constitutional%20figurehead%20except%20in%20three%20areas%2C%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98Super%20CM%E2%80%99%20and%20give%20powers%20to%20the%20LG%20to%20appoint%20heads%20of%20large%20number%20of%20regulatory%20agencies..%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20the%20deliberate%20regression%20from%20a%20people%E2%80%99s%20government%20guaranteed%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Delhi%2030%20years%20ago.%20And%20hence%20it%20is%20a%20decimation%20of%20the%20most%20fundamental%20constitutional%20values%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20reflecting%20on%20the%20selective%20interpretation%20of%20events%20and%20the%20way%20the%20proceedings%20happened%20this%20Monsoon%20Session%20(as%20a%20pattern%20seen%20for%20some%20time%20now)%2C%20one%20can%20only%20reminisce%20how%20in%20the%20current%20governmentality%2C%20there%20are%20elements%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20the%20Raj%2C%20the%20colonial%20British%20administration%2C%20that%20ruled%20India%20for%20over%20two%20centuries%20(first%20by%20Company%20and%20then%20by%20the%20Queen%E2%80%99s%20rule)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fspecials%2Fsunday-spotlight%2Fmodi-governmentality-similar-to-british-raj-s-755088.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eestablishing%20an%20imperial%20umbrella%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20centralising%20and%20consolidating%20power%20via%20law%2C%20language%20and%20knowledge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20systematic%20capture%20of%20institutions%20is%20seen%20amidst%20a%20deep%20retrogression%20in%20democratic%20values%20and%20constitutionally%20safeguarded%20separation%20of%20powers.%20One%20may%20only%20ascertain%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fspecials%2Fsunday-spotlight%2Fmodi-governmentality-similar-to-british-raj-s-755088.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehow%20the%20current%20state%20of%20polity%20in%20India%20closely%20resembles%20the%20lived%20experience%20of%20a%20colonial%20administration%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691984507000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28190125%2FScreenshot-2023-07-28-at-6.59.30-PM_cleanup-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmonsoon-session-parliament-laws-discussion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Not%20only%20is%20there%20a%20crisis%20of%20accountability%2C%20the%20speedy%20passing%20of%20bills%20by%20the%20ruling%20executive%20without%20critical%20discussion%20or%20appropriate%20reflection%20is%20the%20norm%20now.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2