r%20the%202022%20midterms%2C%20the%20GOP%20picked%20up%20four%20House%20seats%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20commanding%2020-8%20statewide%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20an%20ongoing%20legal%20challenge%20to%20the%20state's%20congressional%20maps%20has%20produced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1R2TuSaMYmYz9VNxAHwmWtoo685DVAMRa%2Fview%3Fpli%3D1%5C%22%3Ean%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20restore%20Lawson's%20North%20Florida%20district%20for%20the%202024%20election%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F12%2Fflorida-house-seat-al-lawson-00110962%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Politico%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20agreement%20between%20Florida%20and%20the%20groups%20challenging%20the%20DeSantis-drawn%20congressional%20map%20would%20not%20halt%20litigation%20over%20the%20boundaries%2C%20but%20it%20would%20narrow%20the%20ongoing%20suit%20to%20Lawson's%20district.%20Under%20the%20agreement%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20would%20have%20to%20end%20their%20challenges%20to%20districts%20in%20the%20Orlando%20and%20Tampa%20Bay%20areas%2C%20respectively%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20lawsuit%20involving%20the%20congressional%20maps%20is%20currently%20in%20federal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlivia%20Mendoza%2C%20the%20director%20of%20litigation%20and%20policy%20for%20the%20National%20Redistricting%20Foundation%2C%20praised%20the%20tentative%20agreement%20as%20one%20that%20would%20restore%20an%20element%20of%20fairness%20back%20to%20the%20congressional%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20promising%20step%20forward%20for%20Black%20voters%20whose%20voting%20power%20was%20disgracefully%20targeted%20by%20Gov.%20DeSantis%20in%20his%20quest%20for%20artificial%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Politico.%20%26quot%3BFloridians%20deserve%20fair%20maps%20%E2%80%94%20and%20success%20in%20this%20case%20will%20deliver%20a%20major%20step%20in%20that%20direction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorida%20Republican%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Cord%20Byrd%2C%20a%20defendant%20in%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20told%20Politico%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20comment%20on%20pending%20litigation%20but%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20stipulation%20speaks%20for%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20contingent%20of%20groups%20including%20Black%20Voters%20Matter%2C%20Equal%20Ground%2C%20Florida%20Rising%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flwvfl.org%2Fstate-of-florida-admits-diminishment-of-black-voting-power-in-redistricting-case-agrees-to-path-for-new-remedial-map-for-2024%2F%5C%22%3ELeague%20of%20Women%20Voters%20of%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%20sued%20the%20state%20over%20the%20congressional%20maps%20one%20day%20after%20DeSantis%20signed%20them%20into%20law.%20They%20alleged%20he%20had%20used%20the%20bully%20pulpit%20of%20his%20office%20to%20push%20legislative%20Republicans%20into%20accepting%20his%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Csection%20data-content-section%3D%5C%225%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EA%20trial%20was%20set%20to%20be%20held%20late%20in%20August%2C%20but%20attorneys%20for%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20along%20with%20the%20DeSantis%20administration%20and%20the%20Florida%20legislature%2C%20crafted%20a%20plan%20to%20limit%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EThe%20trial%20is%20now%20set%20to%20focus%20on%20whether%20the%20redistricting%20law%20approved%20by%20Florida%20votes%20violates%20the%20equal%20protection%20clause.%20It%20will%20not%20include%20arguments%20over%20whether%20or%20not%20several%20districts%20were%20constructed%20to%20boost%20Republicans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EUnder%20the%20Fair%20Districts%20provision%20approved%20by%20voters%2C%20districts%20can't%20be%20formulated%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bdiminish%26quot%3B%20the%20opportunity%20for%20minority%20voters%20to%20select%20a%20candidate%20of%20their%20choice.%20But%20when%20DeSantis%20submitted%20his%20own%20map%2C%20he%20tore%20apart%20Lawson's%205th%20Congressional%20District%2C%20which%20ran%20from%20areas%20west%20of%20Tallahassee%20to%20Jacksonville.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EDeSantis%20said%20Lawson's%20district%20was%20unconstitutional%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20was%20an%20illegal%20racial%20gerrymander.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EA%20recent%20decision%20from%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20where%20the%20conservative-dominated%20body%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsupreme-court-redistricting-race-voting-rights-alabama-af0d789ec7498625d344c0a4327367fe%5C%22%3Eruled%20against%3C%2Fa%3E%20weakening%20protections%20of%20the%20Voting%20Rights%20Act%20may%20have%20given%20the%20plaintiffs%20a%20major%20boost%20in%20their%20efforts%20to%20challenge%20the%20DeSantis-drawn%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-content-child-index%3D%5C%220-2%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20agreement%20that%20was%20filed%20late%20last%20week%2C%20attorneys%20for%20the%20governor%20and%20the%20legislature%20stated%20that%20%26quot%3Bnone%20of%20the%20enacted%20districts%20in%20North%20Florida%20are%20districts%20in%20which%20Black%20voters%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20elect%20their%20preferred%20candidates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawson%2C%20who%20ran%20for%20reelection%20in%202022%20and%20lost%20to%20Neal%20Dunn%20in%20the%20heavily%202nd%20Republican%20district%2C%20told%20Politico%20on%20Saturday%20he%20would%20think%20about%20running%20for%20Congress%20again%20should%20his%20old%20district%20be%20restored%20to%20a%20configuration%20similar%20to%20the%20district%20that%20he%20represented%20before%20last%20year's%20midterms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdesantis-democratic-congressional-district-restored-agreement-black-voters-gop-lawson-2023-8%5C%22%3EBus